Description:

Given an unsorted integer array, find the smallest missing positive integer.

Example 1:

Input: [1,2,0]
Output: 3

Solution:
Time complexity : O(n) 0ms


Assume the array's size is n,we can throw away any element that is bigger than n and record element that is bigger than 0 and smaller than or equal to n.Then we can set id = 1 at first ,when id appears in nums,we just add 1 to id, and check if it has appeared

class Solution {
    public int firstMissingPositive(int[] nums) {
        if(nums.length == 0) return 1;
        boolean []ans = new boolean[nums.length + 3];
        int id = 1;
        for(int i = 0;i < nums.length;i++){
            if(nums[i] == id){
                ans[id] = true;
                while(true){
                    if(ans[id])    id++;
                    else break;    
            }
        }
            else if(nums[i] > 0 && nums[i] <= nums.length) ans[nums[i]] = true;
        }
        return id;
    }
}
